items.description:
Get early access to build and test build, be able to try all epochs and test them by yourself on Patreon or contact me for support on Discord

To support me you can buy me a coffe at https://ko-fi.com/antonioriolo

Training settings:

33 images, 15 steps, 10 epochs, you find many epochs (with test images using plot xy script) on my Patreon while supporting me.


Recommended settings:

  • Make sure you are aware on the usage instructions of LORA

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras (Recommended for best quality, you may try other samplers)

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 9

  • LORA weight for txt2img: reccomended 0.5

  • Keys: wearing samba dance dress, carnival party

This model has average difficulty to be used. You just have to play with weights to get what you want. You might want to give a weight to the keyword wearing samba dress dance, 1.2 or 1.3 might be good.

Also you might want to give a weight to the dress color, since it usually draw it in yellow and green.

Example "woman, (wearing samba dress dance:1.2), (red dress:1.2), etc"

carnival keyword doesn't always work, also in this case you might want to give an higher weight to make your woman inside a carnival party, but in most of the cases i tryied it wasn't necessary. carnival or carnival party both should work.

If you'd like to support my efforts and have access to early and bleeding edge builds, please think about joining my Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/betterCuteAsians

items.name: Nature - AutoPrompt - Awesome prompt lists
items.description:
Description


üåøüå∏ Discover a diverse nature image wildcard pack filled with serene gardens, exotic flowers, and breathtaking landscapes. üé® Immerse yourself in impressionist paintings, abstract expressionism, and surreal movie settings. Experience tranquility, enchantment, and the wonders of nature through vibrant colors and artistic mastery. üèîÔ∏èüåå Embark on a visual journey through ethereal mountains, alpine landscapes, and fantasy RPG scenes. From tranquil moments to thought-provoking art, this pack captures the beauty of nature in various styles. üåà‚ú® #NatureArt #Surrealism #Impressionism

Usage

Useful for when you want to create images and later go through and pick out the best creations. These prompts are randomly generated every time I generate new lists.

I use them in conjunction with a stable diffusion image viewer I have written where I view thousands of images I've created to find:

  1. Good prompts that have an art style I like

  2. Good prompts that create really good images

  3. Good compositions

How to use prompt files

  1. Open automatic1111 SD / any other SD creation tool with similar prompt file input

  2. Select <Script> --> Prompts from file or textbox

  3. Drop file or copy paste contents in the "List of prompts inputs"

  4. To view information on images you have created you can use "PNG Info" tab in Automatic1111.

Dataset description

  • Example prompt for garden_masterpiece: Create a magnificent, best quality work of art, In a realm of enchanted serenity, a garden of tranquility blossoms, its Zen-like beauty inducing a sense of inner peace, An inverted world with sky beneath and ground above, defying expectations, vanguardism oil painting

  • Example prompt for flower_garden: Abstract Expressionism, Within an idyllic oasis, a haven of botanical wonders reveals, its exotic flowers a testament to nature's diversity, spill light, Grunge

  • Example prompt for landscape_composition: A secluded mountain valley with a meandering river and wildflowers in bloom, Complementary, Zoom In, Impressionist, spill light, background light, The explosion unleashes a powerful shockwave, causing the ground to tremble and structures to crumble

  • Example prompt for art_prompt_artist_flowers_weather: A snow-covered alpine landscape with evergreen trees and a frozen lake, Pastel Painting, Orchid, engaging, Paul Strand, A stormy day with dark clouds and thunder booming in the distance

  • Example prompt for fantasy_landscape: magical, Skyborne archipelago with cloud forests and floating fauna, Tetradic, spotlight, cloudy, tungsten

  • Example prompt for painted_landscape: Captivating, A calm lake with a small boat and reflections of the sky, Leonardo da Vinci, Impressionism

  • Example prompt for surrealist_movie_landscape: A sun-drenched field of lavender with a rustic stone cottage, A thought-provoking and darkly humorous horror film, Assemblage, Lustrous luster that bestows a rich and captivating sheen

  • Example prompt for art_prompt_artist_flowers: A charming European village nestled in a valley with colorful houses, Printmaking, Gerbera, Impressive, Dali

  • Example prompt for fantasy_rpg_landscape: Surrealist Art, Fabled and legendary, A towering waterfall, cascading down from a majestic peak into a sparkling pool, key light, fluorescent, candlelight

  • Example prompt for mountains_images: Ethereal mountain scene, autumn, Expansive plateaus, Rivers

Feedback

If you got feedback just comment.

items.name: Reshiram Lora
items.description:
This is a lora for only anthropomorphic/anthroified/pokemorph reshirams. Reasoning given at end.

This has been updated to the finished release and I recommend it over the original; while I couldn't find more good images that didn't corrupt it in any way, 2 more epochs with some closeups on the heads to improve eye and hair quality did have an effect. Also, it can do males easier now and the chance of huge badonkers jumpscare is lessened, but still a threat.

Also, image #3 is black because I wanted to recreate a bad gen form an earlier model that looked cool and to end racism.

Use with any AnythingV3-based models and a strength of 0.7-0.8.

Tagging just "reshiram" works well, but if the chokers or feathers give you an issue then include some of these: white body, feathered body, winged arms/feathered arms, feathered wings/arm tuft, chokers, white hair, long hair, finger claws, tail/big tail. Tags with slashes should be used alternatively since they aren't meant to mix. The entire internet has also decided that reshiram is a milf, so male tags need a little extra weight, muscular helps as well or just using negatives for female features. No ferals, reasoning below.

As for the lack of regular non-bait reshiram:

I originally had a mix of feral and anthroified content in the dataset, and while it wasn't polluted by any specific images it seemed to have weird results even with an extreme anthroified bias. Forcing ((((feral)))) and negating pokemorph and anthroified did work, but the results all had four legs or turned into an anthro reshiram with a reshiram-horse hybrid (very good results but weird). Furry models were "better" but still put feral reshiram on four legs or cut it in half (???). I continued working on it and tweaking tags until I realized something: no one uploads sample images for my work, likely because it's too raunchy to post. I thought of that in the context of what's basically just an animal, and after a long 12 seconds of staring into space I wiped the feral images off of my drive and retrained without them. Instantly fixed everything and upped quality to boot. I might be a degenerate freak, but I have standards and will not create something that even tangentially might lead to beastiality/zoophilia content. Sure, it's an imaginary animal, but that doesn't change much and I don't feel comfortable with that. From here on out, any Lora's I create will only be of humans and anthros. I will commit degeneracy in the name of BIG FUNNY but I will never stoop to perversion.

TLDR: I'm not evil, just insane. I draw the line here, thanks for understanding.

items.name: Mieruko-chan - multiple characters
items.description:
LoRA trained on NAI with screencaps from the anime series Mieruko-chan, and some additional fan art. It can generate 4 characters + ghosts.

Please rate and give me some feedback if you'd like to see more of these models. And let me know if it needs improvement.

How to use:

  • Trigger words for the characters: yotsuya miko, yurikawa hana, niguredou julia, and as a small bonus with much less data, yotsuya kyousuke. You can also prompt just ghosts (using dark aura and black eyes can help with the ghost effect). See image gallery for reference (generated with Hassaku model).

  • Recommended 1.0 weight and your usual CFG. Reduce CFG/weight if in some models like AOM2 gets a bit blurry, and/or use hires fix.

  • It is not easy to generate the different characters in the same image without some details wrong. Perhaps latent couple or inpainting would help.

  • When prompting for ghosts you should also include male tags like 1boy or multiple boys. Proper prompting is required to keep ghosts and characters separate. Otherwise you can get characters as ghosts. If that's your thing, it works great :)

Characters (images below generated with AnyLora):

yotsuya miko

yurikawa hana

niguredou julia

yotsuya kyousuke

Additional info

I make these models for fun and for the challenge and release them for free for everyone to enjoy, for non-commercial use (see license). The one thing I ask of you is to provide rating and feedback! That helps me understand where I can improve and helps me stay motivated to produce more content!

I accept suggestions or requests here or on Civitai discord server.

If you like my contributions to the community, please consider Buying Me A Coffee or check out my other sites on AllMyLinks

TRAINING INFO

Trained on 16 photos
1600 steps
1 epoch

RECOMMENDED SETTINGS

For txt2img, a weight of 0.7-0.9 will give a little more flexibility, but 1.0 isn't bad. A weight of 1.0 works really well for inpainting. Face restoration isn't usually necessary, but I recommend setting your face restoration strength inside auto1111 settings to something like 0.7-0.8.

GETTING THE BEST LIKENESS WITH LORA'S

The checkpoint you use can heavily influence the likeness of a celebrity Lora. I train my Lora's on SD15, so you'll get the best likeness on any model that used SD15 as the base model. See this example for how a checkpoint can influence the look of a Lora.

items.name: Massakasama Style
items.description:
A quite distinct colorful style with a chibi touch

How to use
Just prompt away, even just 1girl works if you're uninspired.

Req weights (approx):
AOM2 and probably other with more 3D style mixed in: 1.2 - 1.3
NAI: 0.8 - 1.0

Works good with "simple background" or "[random color] background" tags. "Outline" is another one to try.
You can also put "simple background" in negatives if you want more detailed ones. Other negatives are "greyscale" and "monochrome" to make the colors pop out more if your VAE don't do it for you.

Don't forget to review and upload your own images, it's always fun to see what you're creating!
Like my LoRAs and want more? Please consider a small tip towards my electricity bill and further training >.<

Misc
Trained on NAI at 512 res. Dataset of 410 images.
All images are raw (slightly cherrypicked), txt2img gens, no post work done.

Version 3.0 Description:

Pleased to introduce the 3.0 version of the XXMix_9 series. This version has significantly improved in versatility and support for LORA, and the hand performance is significantly better than the previous versions. The 3.0 version is a mix of v2.5, v2.6, and XXMix_4. When generating images, I try not to use any Embedding models as much as possible because I have found that some Embedding models are more obscure, and you don't know which ones are working and which ones are not, which makes it difficult to restore the example.

If you want to restore the example, please install the following extensions first:

Adetailer (https://github.com/Bing-su/adetailer): It is recommended to always enable it when generating images. If you want to restore the example by more than 90%, it is recommended to check whether Adetailer is enabled in the image information.

CFG Scale Fix (https://github.com/mcmonkeyprojects/sd-dynamic-thresholding): Enable it when needed, it will improve the quality of the image. I use the default value of about 7. If it is daytime, the CFG value can be slightly larger, and at night, the value should be smaller. (After my test, I cannot restore the example 100% on the second computer. I still don't know the reason. It may be a problem with the CFG Scale Fix extension or the block VAE. However, you can basically restore it to about 90%-95%, and the impact on the image is not significant.)

For generating images, here is my personal experience: If you get a picture that you really like, but there are serious problems with the hands or other parts, and you don't want to use local redraw to modify it, then it is recommended to adjust the CFG value slightly (0.2-0.3 range) after fixing the seed. This way, you may get a perfect picture while keeping the original image.

Here, I would like to share a suffix sentence that I like, which can make the image more expressive. Of course, you can modify the words in the sentence to fine-tune the image style. These words include: fantasy, high contrast, ink strokes, explosions, overexposure, purple and red tone impression, abstract, brush strokes ((watercolor painting by John Berkey and Jeremy Mann)), negative space.

This is a model related to the "Picture of the Week" contest on Stable Diffusion discord.

You can find this dataset in a more complete model, SDArt : Complete Edition.

I try to make a model out of all the submissions, for people to continue enjoy the theme after the event, and see a little of their designs in other people's creations. The token stays "SDArt" and I balance the learning on the low side, so that it doesn't just replicate creations.

The pictures were tagged using the token "SDArt", and an arbitrary token given to the user that submitted it.

The dataset is available below and is composed of 36 pictures.

What if the world was in the palm of your hands? Condensed, contained, and captured within a simple sphere for all to see?

  • Bring your miniature world to life. Big things come in small packages!

  • A world made of crystals and moss? A lush forest landscape? An upside-down world? A world made of instruments? A world made of tangled wires? Be creative! Be uniquely you!

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight according to the instructions (by default it's :1)

Make a regular 512x image and manually upscale it through image to image. If you need to use hires fix I used Uniscale balanced and UltraSharpX4 they looked okay but changed the face a bit.

trained on "a woman" I would recommend not using any photo jargon starting prompt with "a photo of" just start every prompt with a woman and go into details, but do whatever you want blud.

Weight: 1.0

Default Outfit: kyriedef, hair over one eye, glasses, jacket, black dress, red necktie, pantyhose

Add pink hair and purple eyes if necessary.

The results of your generations are dependent on the additional LoRAs, weights, and models you use, so it may not work or come out as consistent as my sample images. Other reasons may include me using xformers, token merging, and a modified DPM++ 2M Karras sampler. You may sometimes notice that my prompt includes <lyco:. Note that some of my LoRA files are located within my LyCORIS folder. If the model is labeled as a LoRA, it's a simple LoRA. If it's specified as a LyCORIS, it's a LoCon/LoHa.

items.name: Jolyne - JoJo's Bizarre Adventure
items.description:
This v2 should finally work better with full body shots, but keep in mind this model is mainly thought for medium shots, portraits and closeups. JoJo faces have way too many expression lines, so SD messes up trying to simplify them. With high resolutions, it should work fine, though.

Trigger: 'Jolyne_Anime'

Optional tags: 'coat', 'pants', 'face focus', '(((pink hair)))' -> (for the "alternate pallet" effect)

Weight: [0.6 - 0.9]. Go high for a strong art style (with less flexibility), and low for creative uses or poses (and even lower for realism). With closeups, the art style should remain consistent until around 0.65.

Suggestion: Experiment with lights, colors and visual effects. Some results can be quite interesting!

Checkpoints used in examples: 'Anything V5' and 'UHD-23'

______

Example prompt:

Jolyne_anime, confident, ready to fight, creative shot, green eyes, green lips, perfect quality, (absurdres), 4k, masterpiece, lens flare, light rays, (psychedelic background), illustration, ((anime screenshot)), professional lighting, posing for viewer, ((psychedelia, face focus, wind, detailed face)) + [LoRA set to 0.65]
